---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
import CodeBlock from "../../components/CodeBlock.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="RTL Support" description="Full RTL layout mirroring for Arabic, Hebrew, and Farsi. Grid, nav, forms, and utilities mirror automatically with dir=rtl.">
  <section class="padding-top-extra padding-bottom-extra border-bottom">
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase color-blue">Internationalization</p>
    <h1 class="text-balance">RTL Support</h1>
    <p class="lead no-orphan">
      Full right-to-left layout mirroring for Arabic, Hebrew, Farsi, and other
      RTL languages. Add <code>dir="rtl"</code> to your <code>&lt;html&gt;</code>
      element and ply handles the rest.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="padding-top-extra padding-bottom-extra border-bottom" id="basic">
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase color-blue">Setup</p>
    <h2>Basic Usage</h2>
    <p class="no-orphan">
      Set <code>dir="rtl"</code> on the <code>&lt;html&gt;</code> element for a
      full page RTL layout, or on any container for scoped RTL.
    </p>

    <CodeBlock code={`<!-- Full page RTL -->
<html lang="ar" dir="rtl">

<!-- Scoped RTL section -->
<div dir="rtl">
  <p>This content flows right-to-left.</p>
</div>`} />
  </section>

  <section class="padding-top-extra padding-bottom-extra border-bottom" id="grid">
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase color-blue">Layout</p>
    <h2>Grid Mirroring</h2>
    <p class="no-orphan">
      The grid system automatically mirrors in RTL mode. Columns that start
      from the left will start from the right instead.
    </p>

    <div class="border border-radius padding">
      <p class="text-sm text-secondary">LTR (default):</p>
      <div class="units-row bottom-margin">
        <div class="unit-25"><div class="bg-blue-pastel padding-sm border-radius text-center text-sm">Sidebar</div></div>
        <div class="unit-75"><div class="bg-surface-alt padding-sm border-radius text-center text-sm">Main Content</div></div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-sm text-secondary">RTL (<code>dir="rtl"</code>):</p>
      <div dir="rtl">
        <div class="units-row">
          <div class="unit-25"><div class="bg-blue-pastel padding-sm border-radius text-center text-sm">الشريط الجانبي</div></div>
          <div class="unit-75"><div class="bg-surface-alt padding-sm border-radius text-center text-sm">المحتوى الرئيسي</div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <CodeBlock code={`<div dir="rtl">
  <div class="units-row">
    <div class="unit-25">Sidebar</div>
    <div class="unit-75">Main Content</div>
  </div>
</div>`} />
  </section>

  <section class="padding-top-extra padding-bottom-extra border-bottom" id="navigation">
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase color-blue">Components</p>
    <h2>Navigation</h2>
    <p class="no-orphan">
      Navbars automatically mirror in RTL. Items align to the right and flow leftward.
    </p>

    <div class="border border-radius padding">
      <div dir="rtl">
        <nav class="navbar">
          <ul>
            <li class="active"><a href="#navigation">الرئيسية</a></li>
            <li><a href="#navigation">حول</a></li>
            <li><a href="#navigation">اتصل بنا</a></li>
          </ul>
        </nav>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="padding-top-extra padding-bottom-extra border-bottom" id="forms">
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase color-blue">Components</p>
    <h2>Forms</h2>
    <p class="no-orphan">
      Form labels align right, select arrows flip to the left side, and
      input groups reverse their prepend/append order.
    </p>

    <div class="border border-radius padding">
      <div dir="rtl">
        <form class="form">
          <label>
            البريد الإلكتروني
            <input type="email" placeholder="user@example.com" />
          </label>
          <label>
            الدولة
            <select>
              <option>المملكة العربية السعودية</option>
              <option>الإمارات العربية المتحدة</option>
              <option>مصر</option>
            </select>
          </label>
          <button class="btn btn-blue" type="submit">إرسال</button>
        </form>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="padding-top-extra padding-bottom-extra border-bottom" id="utilities">
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase color-blue">Mirrored</p>
    <h2>Mirrored Utilities</h2>
    <p class="no-orphan">
      Directional utilities like <code>margin-left</code>, <code>padding-right</code>,
      <code>float-left</code>, <code>text-left</code>, and <code>text-right</code>
      are automatically mirrored inside <code>dir="rtl"</code>.
    </p>

    <table class="table-stroked">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>LTR Class</th><th>RTL Behavior</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>text-left</code></td><td>Becomes <code>text-align: right</code></td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>text-right</code></td><td>Becomes <code>text-align: left</code></td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>margin-left</code></td><td>Becomes <code>margin-right</code></td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>margin-right</code></td><td>Becomes <code>margin-left</code></td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>margin-left-auto</code></td><td>Becomes <code>margin-right: auto</code></td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>float-left</code></td><td>Becomes <code>float: right</code></td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>float-right</code></td><td>Becomes <code>float: left</code></td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section class="padding-top-extra padding-bottom-extra border-bottom" id="logical">
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase color-blue">Bidirectional</p>
    <h2>Logical Property Helpers</h2>
    <p class="no-orphan">
      For truly bidirectional layouts, use CSS logical property utilities that
      work correctly in both LTR and RTL without mirroring overrides.
    </p>

    <table class="table-stroked">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Class</th><th>Description</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>margin-inline-start</code></td><td>Margin on the start side (left in LTR, right in RTL)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>margin-inline-end</code></td><td>Margin on the end side (right in LTR, left in RTL)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>padding-inline-start</code></td><td>Padding on the start side</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>padding-inline-end</code></td><td>Padding on the end side</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>border-inline-start</code></td><td>Border on the start side</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>border-inline-end</code></td><td>Border on the end side</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <CodeBlock code={`<!-- Works in both LTR and RTL automatically -->
<div class="margin-inline-start padding-inline-end">
  Content with directional spacing
</div>`} />
  </section>

  <section class="padding-top-extra padding-bottom-extra" id="opt-out">
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase color-blue">Control</p>
    <h2>Opting Out</h2>
    <p class="no-orphan">
      Use <code>no-rtl</code> on any element inside an RTL context to force
      LTR direction. Useful for code blocks, phone numbers, or other content
      that should always be left-to-right.
    </p>

    <div class="border border-radius padding">
      <div dir="rtl">
        <p>هذا النص يتدفق من اليمين إلى اليسار.</p>
        <pre class="no-rtl"><code>const greeting = "Hello, World!";</code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>

    <CodeBlock code={`<div dir="rtl">
  <p>Arabic text flows right-to-left.</p>
  <pre class="no-rtl"><code>Code stays left-to-right.</code></pre>
</div>`} />
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
